main event: Two unidentified flying objects were observed flying in a westerly direction over Lakeport, California on July 22, 1956.
interesting points: The objects were visually observed for three to four seconds., The objects were described as luminous and flying at an estimated speed of 600 miles per hour., The report stated there was insufficient data for evaluation due to the briefness of the sighting., A former scientist reported a similar sighting, describing a round object hovering for several minutes., The weather during the sightings was clear, which contributed to the visibility of the objects.
witness description: a former scientist from Berkeley, California
